        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 27 at 4:41PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 440 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Coaldale, or near Matoaka, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail and wind gusts up to 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Loose objects may be knocked over due to wind gusts.

Locations impacted include...
Matoaka...
Pocahontas...
Bramwell...
Montcalm...
Coaldale...
Pinnacle Rock State Park...
and Boissevain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
